    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i see what u mean about the cost and safety stuff, but if we're looking at the urgency of the climate crisis, some people say that ignoring nuclear is basically ignoring the only realistic way to decarbonize the grid fast enough. do u think that's a valid way to look at it, or is that an exaggeration?",
